## Writing patterns that work

### Headlines

THWB headlines are often declarative and sometimes poetic.

Examples:
- "A home is built on purpose, or it isn't built at all."
- "The cost of winging it."
- "On Sunday meetings that actually work."

Trellis headlines are direct and promise-forward.

Examples:
- "The operating system for families who want to build on purpose."
- "Eleven pillars. One app. A calmer, more intentional home."
- "Kids aren't an afterthought. They're half the house."

### Subheads

Short. Clarifying. Almost always one sentence.

### Body copy

Three-sentence paragraphs are ideal.
Occasionally a single sentence stands alone.
Occasionally a five-sentence paragraph breathes.
Rhythm matters more than consistency.

### CTAs (Trellis specifically)

- "Start your family" (primary, recurring)
- "See how it works"
- "Try the free tour"
- "Keep reading" (rare)

Never: "Click here" / "Learn more" / "Submit"

### Callouts and eyebrows

All caps, letter-spacing 0.2em, small size (12-14px), gold or
muted forest. Used sparingly to structure longer pages.

